msgid "Recommended Additional Indexes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:148
msgid "``alias``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:150
msgid ""
"Kolab Groupware by default uses the ``alias`` attribute to store "
"additional recipient email addresses for users. This attribute is not "
"indexed by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:154
msgid "``mailAlternateAddress``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:156
msgid ""
"While the ``mailAlternateAddress`` is used, by default, as a container of"
" any external email addresses for a user (such as a private or personal "
"email address), you may find it is searched as part of auto-completion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:161
msgid ""
"Especially when using VLV/SSS, should the ``mailAlternateAddress`` "
"attribute index be a substring index, but it only contains an equality "
"index by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:168
msgid "Configuring Virtual List View Control"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:170
msgid ""
"Virtual List View features in the LDAP server aid in listing pre-indexed "
"and pre-sorted LDAP entries in a paginated fashion, and is a required "
"configuration item for deployments with over 1.000 entries in their LDAP "
"hierarchies [#]_, when also using an address book, auto-completion and/or"
" the Web Administration Panel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:176
msgid ""
"On the side of the LDAP server, Virtual List Views consist of two "
"separate configuration items:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:179
msgid "The search, with a base dn, scope and filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:181
msgid "The index that includes the Server-Side Sorting parameters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:183
msgid ""
"For an LDAP client to successfully use Virtual List View controls, it is "
"crucially important that:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:186
msgid ""
"The search base dn and scope match the configuration of the VLV search, "
"and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:189
msgid ""
"Any attributes searched in addition to the configured VLV search filter "
"are appropriately indexed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:192
msgid ""
"By default, the configuration of primarily the Kolab web client uses the "
"following configuration parameters for browsing the LDAP address book:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:196
msgid "For Individual Contact Entries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:197
msgid "**Search Base DN**: *ou=People,$root_dn*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:199
#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:236
msgid ""
"where *$root_dn* is the relevant root suffix, such as "
"``dc=example,dc=org``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:202
#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:239
msgid "**Search Scope**: *sub*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:203
msgid "**Search Filter**: *(objectClass=inetOrgPerson)*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:207
msgid ""
"The search parameters for address book entries are deliberately **not** "
"limited to only include other Kolab user entries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:210
#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:248
msgid ""
"The configuration for the LDAP address book also lists the order of "
"attributes to use when sorting the entries:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:213
msgid "displayname,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:214
msgid "sn,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:215
msgid "givenname,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:216
#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:251
msgid "cn"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:218
msgid ""
"This configures the LDAP server to first attempt sorting by "
"``displayname`` attribute value, then ``sn``, then ``givenname``, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:221
msgid ""
"When two entries hold the same value for an attribute used with sorting, "
"the next attribute configured for sorting is used, if any."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:224
msgid ""
"When configuring the sorting attributes, only use combinations of "
"meaningful attributes, and preferrably as few as possible at a time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:227
msgid ""
"When, for example, you want one list to be sorted by user's names, and "
"another list sorted by phone number, do not combine the two different "
"lists in to one sorting configuration. Instead, use multiple values for "
"the ``vlvSort`` attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:233
msgid "For Groups"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:234
msgid "**Search Base DN**: *ou=Groups,$root_dn*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:240
msgid ""
"**Search Filter**: "
"*(|(objectClass=groupOfUniqueNames)(objectClass=groupOfUrls))*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administrator-guide/tweaking-389ds.rst:244
msgid ""
"For groups too, the search parameters for address book entries are "
"deliberately **not** limited to only include other Kolab user entries."
msgstr ""

